=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect p-phenylenediamine as p-diacetamidobenzene (Ac2O) to give the bis-acetanilide needed for controlled electrophilic substitution. | Step 2: Friedel–Crafts succinylation of p-diacetamidobenzene with succinic anhydride/AlCl3 gives the β-keto acid 3-(2,5-bis(acetamido)benzoyl)propionic acid. | Step 3: Intramolecular cyclization of this keto acid with PPA or conc. H2SO4 forms 5,8-bis(acetamido)-3,4-dihydronaphthalen-1(2H)-one (the 5,8-bis(acetamido)-1-tetralone core). | Step 4: Hydrolyze the two acetamides (aq. HCl or aq. NaOH, then workup) to unmask both anilines and obtain Nc1ccc2c(c1N)CCC2=O.

